# project

- project is set up and ready for development

# requirements

## user-constraints
- project slug is naiou @spec
- local project lives at /home/everlier/code/naiou @spec

## cli
- the app launches from a naiou command @draft

## scaffold
- the app uses OpenTUI infrastructure and scaffold patterns from /home/everlier/code/skilled without copying skilled app logic or screens @draft

## visuals
- the app adapts the hyperspace effect from /home/everlier/code/opentui-candy @draft
- the hyperspace tunnel turns green for Yes and red for No when the decision is ready @draft
- the final scene exits hyperspace into normal star colors and scales a shaded planet into view with Yes or No written on it @draft

## agent
- the app adapts the agentic loop and configuration patterns from /home/everlier/code/mi @draft
- the agent replies with exactly Yes or No @draft
- the agent uses structured outputs to narrow the final decision @draft
- the agent has tools and may explore before finalizing a decision @draft

## flow
- launching naiou initially shows a space scene @draft
- typed questions render as large centered ASCII characters occupying roughly the central 70 percent of the terminal @draft
- the input view includes a blinking large ASCII cursor @draft
- pressing Enter starts the agent loop and hyperspace animation @draft
- a tiny greyed-out status line appears at the top during agent processing @draft
